@page "/mt"

<Title Size="3">More Tools</Title>

<Row>
    <Column ColumnSize="ColumnSize.Is4.OnTablet.Is3.OnWidescreen.Is12.OnMobile">
        <Card Margin="Margin.Is4.OnY">
            <CardImage Source="assets/images/placeholder.jpg"/>
            <CardBody>
                <CardTitle Size="5">Favicon Generator</CardTitle>
                <CardText>
                    With so many platforms and icons, it's hard to know exactly what you should do.
                    What are the dimensions of favicon.ico? How many Touch icons do I need? This tool
                    did the reseach and testing for you. Each platform comes with its own design requirements.
                    You can't just use the same picture everywhere. This tool also knows this and lets you craft
                    your icons platform per platform.
                </CardText>
            </CardBody>
            <CardBody>
                <Button Color="Color.Primary" Type="ButtonType.Link" To="https://realfavicongenerator.net">Use Now</Button>
            </CardBody>
        </Card>
    </Column>
    <Column ColumnSize="ColumnSize.Is4.OnTablet.Is3.OnWidescreen.Is12.OnMobile">
        <Card Margin="Margin.Is4.OnY">
            <CardImage Source="assets/images/placeholder.jpg"/>
            <CardBody>
                <CardTitle Size="5">Reqbin</CardTitle>
                <CardText>
                    ReqBin is an online API testing tool for REST and SOAP APIs. Test API endpoints by making
                    API requests directly from your browser. Test API responses with built-in JSON and XML validators.
                    Load test your API with hundreds of simulated concurrent connections. Generate code snippets for
                    API automation testing frameworks. Share and discuss your API requests online.
                </CardText>
            </CardBody>
            <CardBody>
                <Button Color="Color.Primary" Type="ButtonType.Link" To="https://reqbin.com">Use Now</Button>
            </CardBody>
        </Card>
    </Column>
    <Column ColumnSize="ColumnSize.Is4.OnTablet.Is3.OnWidescreen.Is12.OnMobile">
